div.h2: 8259A Dual-PIC Cascade Vector Remapping & EOI Protocol

g.text: BEFORE REMAP (BROKEN default IBM PC mapping)

div.p: ICW1 Port 0x20 & 0xA0 0x11 Cascade mode; ICW4 required io_wait()
ICW2 Port 0x21 0x20 (master base=32) Port 0xA1 0x28 (slave base=40) io_wait()
ICW3 Port 0x21 0x04 (slave on IRQ2, bitmask) Port 0xA1 0x02 (cascade identity=2, binary) io_wait()
ICW4 Port 0x21 0x01 (8086 mode) Port 0xA1 0x01 (8086 mode) io_wait()
Mask restore Port 0x21 0xFC (unmask IRQ0+IRQ1) Port 0xA1 0xFF (all slave masked)

IRQ0 vec 8 = #DF Double Fault IRQ1 vec 9 = Coprocessor Overrun IRQ2 vec 10 = Invalid TSS IRQ3 vec 11 = Segment Not Present IRQ4 vec 12 = Stack Fault IRQ5 vec 13 = #GP General Protection IRQ6 vec 14 = #PF Page Fault IRQ7 vec 15 = Reserved
Master vecs 3239 IRQ0 vec 32 (PIT Timer) IRQ1 vec 33 (Keyboard) IRQ2 vec 34 (Cascade) IRQ3 vec 35 IRQ4 vec 36 IRQ5 vec 37 IRQ6 vec 38 IRQ7 vec 39 (LPT1/Spurious)
Slave vecs 4047 IRQ8 vec 40 (RTC) IRQ9 vec 41 IRQ10 vec 42 IRQ11 vec 43 IRQ12 vec 44 (PS/2 Mouse) IRQ13 vec 45 IRQ14 vec 46 (Primary ATA) IRQ15 vec 47 (Secondary/Spurious)
IRQ8IRQ15 (Slave + Master): outb(0xA0, 0x20) slave EOI first outb(0x20, 0x20) master EOI second (releases cascade IRQ2 on master)
IRQ7 spurious check: outb(0x20, 0x0B) read master ISR If bit 7 NOT set spurious, NO EOI If bit 7 set real IRQ7, send EOI
IRQ15 spurious check: outb(0xA0, 0x0B) read slave ISR If bit 15 NOT set spurious: EOI to master ONLY (0x20) If bit 15 set real IRQ15, both EOIs
